---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { externalLinks } from '../../config';
---

<Layout title="Annex A — Terms of Reference">
  <p class="text-sm text-ink-subtle"><a href="/specification">← Specification</a></p>
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-2">Annex A — Terms of Reference</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-ink-subtle mb-8">
    Plain-language rewriting of ISO 24229 Annex A. The canonical source is
    the <a href={externalLinks.iso24229Standard} class="underline">published standard</a>.
  </p>

  <section id="scope" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.1 Scope</h2>
    <p>
      The Registration Authority (RA) is the body responsible for maintaining
      the public register of conversion-system codes on behalf of ISO/TC 46/WG 3.
      Its scope covers assignment of new codes, processing of deprecation
      requests, and publication of the authoritative register.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="organisation" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.2 Organisation</h2>
    <p>
      The RA is operated jointly by CalConnect and Ribose Inc., under the
      oversight of an Advisory Group (AG) designated by ISO/TC 46/WG 3.
      The AG is convened by Mr. Peeter Päll of Estonia.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3">
      The AG meets bimonthly to review submissions and deprecations.
      Decisions require a simple majority of voting members.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="responsibilities" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.3 Responsibilities</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Maintain the public register at <a href="https://www.iso24229.org" class="underline">www.iso24229.org</a>.</li>
      <li>Validate that each submission meets the eligibility criteria in §5 of the standard.</li>
      <li>Assign code elements in accordance with the structure defined in §4.</li>
      <li>Process deprecation requests and reserve deprecated codes for backwards compatibility.</li>
      <li>Publish meeting minutes and decisions of the AG.</li>
      <li>Liaise with the ISO 639 RA and the ISO 15924 maintainer on cross-standard issues.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="authorities" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.4 Conversion system authorities</h2>
    <p>
      Authorities recognised by the AG maintain their own conversion systems.
      Each authority must designate two authorised persons who can submit
      changes on its behalf. The register publishes the authority's name,
      address, and the names of its authorised persons (contact details
      are not published without consent).
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3">
      See <a href="/register/authority" class="underline">the authority directory</a>
      for the current list.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="submissions" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.5 Submissions</h2>
    <p>
      Submissions are made via structured GitHub issues against the
      <a href="https://github.com/iso24229/iso24229-register" class="underline">register data repository</a>.
      Every submission must include:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
      <li>The proposed code, decomposed into its four segments.</li>
      <li>ISO 639 and ISO 15924 codes for source and target (validated against reference data).</li>
      <li>A specification document (PDF or canonical URL).</li>
      <li>Evidence of real-world use (at least one URL).</li>
      <li>A Unicode-style justification (200+ words).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3">
      See <a href="/apply" class="underline">Apply</a> for the entry points.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="lifecycle" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.6 Lifecycle</h2>
    <p>
      Each system-code moves through the following states:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
      <li><strong>proposed</strong> — submitted, awaiting AG review at the next bimonthly meeting.</li>
      <li><strong>stable</strong> — approved by the AG; the code is reserved.</li>
      <li><strong>deprecated</strong> — superseded or no longer recommended; code reserved for backwards compatibility.</li>
      <li><strong>withdrawn</strong> — removed from active use; code never reused.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section id="review" class="border-t border-line py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">A.7 Review</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms of Reference are reviewed annually by the AG. Material
      changes are forwarded to ISO/TC 46/WG 3 for ratification.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
